org.sbml.jsbml
Class SBMLWriter

java.lang.Object
  org.sbml.jsbml.SBMLWriter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable
public class SBMLWriter
extends Object
implements Cloneable, Serializable

Provides methods for writing SBML to files, text strings or streams.

This SBMLWriter is just a wrapper for the actual implementation in SBMLWriter.

This class is provided for compatibility with libSBML and to avoid problems if the internal of jsbml change, so it is preferable to use it instead of directly using SBMLWriter. The SBMLWriter class is the converse of SBMLReader, and provides the main interface for serializing SBML models into XML and writing the result to files and text strings. The methods for writing SBML all take an SBMLDocument object and a destination.

setProgramName

public int setProgramName(String name)
Sets the name of this program, i.e., the program that is about to write out the SBMLDocument.

If the program name and version are set (see setProgramVersion(String version)), the following XML comment, intended for human consumption, will be written at the beginning of the document: 

           <!-- Created by <program name> version <program version>
           on yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm with JSBML version <JSBML version>. -->

Parameters:
name - the name of this program (where 'this program' refers to the program in which JSBML is embedded, not JSBML itself!)

Returns:
integer value indicating success/failure of the function. The possible values returned by this function are:
  • JSBML.OPERATION_SUCCESS

    See Also:
    setProgramVersion(String version)

    • setProgramVersion

    Sets the version of this program, i.e., the program that is about to write out the SBMLDocument.

 version <JSBML version>. -->

    write

    public void write(SBMLDocument sbmlDocument,
                  File file)
           throws javax.xml.stream.XMLStreamException,
                  SBMLException,
                  IOException
    Writes the given SBML document to a File. If specified in the constructor of this SBMLWriter, the programName and programVersion of the calling program will be made persistent in the resulting SBML File.

    Parameters:
    sbmlDocument - the SBMLDocument to be written
    file - the file where the SBML document is to be written.
    Throws:
    javax.xml.stream.XMLStreamException - if any problems prevent to write the SBMLDocument as XML.
    SBMLException - if any SBML problems prevent to write the SBMLDocument.
    IOException - if it is not possible to write to the given file, e.g., due to an invalid file name or missing permissions.
